DEVELOPER DOCUMENTATION (Technical Guide)
Project Overview
This project digitizes the José Rizal Guided Walk into an interactive virtual tour using multimedia, 3D assets, and web-based tools.

Technologies Used
•	Thinglink (interactive platform)
•	GitHub (version control)
•	360° camera (image capture)
•	3D renders (PNG, MP4)

Asset Management
•	3D renders stored in Media/3D-model/
•	Images and videos stored in Media/
•	Game-related assets stored in Games/ and Thinglink/GamesThinglink/

How to Update the Virtual Tour (Thinglink)
1.	Upload 360° images to Thinglink
2.	Add tags to scenes
3.	Link tags to:
o	Text
o	Audio
o	Video
o	External content
4.	Save and publish updates

Adding New Content
•	Add new images to Media/
•	Add 3D renders if needed
•	Update documentation files
•	Maintain consistent naming conventions

Game Development
•	Game concepts defined in Games/InkedGame.md
•	Assets stored in related folders if needed
•	Integration handled via Thinglink

Collaboration Workflow
•	Clear folder structure for assets
•	Communication with international partners

Deployment
•	Hosted via Thinglink platform
•	Accessible via web browser
•	No backend deployment required

Future Improvements
•	Integrate AI-based storytelling (video)

Maintenance Guidelines
•	Keep assets organized
•	Optimize media for performance
•	Regularly test compatibility (mobile & desktop)
•	Ensure historical and cultural accuracy

